# .dockerignore — anything listed here is NOT included in the build
# context, so `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile won't pull it in. We use
# this as the single source of truth for "what doesn't ship to
# production" — adding a new top-level file or directory now ships by
# default (the inverse of the old explicit-list-in-Dockerfile model
# that kept biting us as trap #1 in CLAUDE.md).
#
# Two rules of thumb when adding here:
#   1. Anything the running app needs at request-time MUST NOT be
#      excluded (admin/, demo/, lib/, server/, prisma/, top-level
#      *.html / *.css / *.js, etc.).
#   2. Anything that's purely dev / docs / dev infra (tests, build
#      outputs, IDE files, design source, markdown other than the
#      ones a route reads) SHOULD be excluded — keeps the image slim
#      and the build context cheap to upload to the remote builder.

# --- never ship: deps the deps stage installs from package.json -----
node_modules
package-lock.json.lock

# --- VCS + IDE -----
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# --- agent / project memory not relevant to runtime -----
.claude
.cursor

# --- env files (secrets must come via fly secrets, not the image) ---
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# --- dev-only top-level docs / planning files ---
README.md
CLAUDE.md
TESTING.md
ROADMAP.md
BUGS.md
LICENSE
LICENSE.md

# --- dev-only top-level config not used at runtime ---
Makefile
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.override.yml
docker-compose.prod.yml
cloudbuild.yaml
fly.toml

# --- dev runtime artefacts (uploads etc. live in /data on Fly) ---
var
prisma/dev.db*
*.log

# --- subdirs the app doesn't touch at runtime ---
docs
design
design_handoff_compass
email
infra
mobile
scripts
security
tests

# --- log / temp files ---
*.tmp
.tmp-*
